cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.PL 

This paper focuses on a specific problem in software engineering, namely incomplete/hidden requirements, and analyzes survey data from software organizations in Austria and Brazil. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses mitigation actions and prevention strategies, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of graphical representations to document causes and solutions could also relate to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
